	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Louisville</placeName> <date>January 2d 1849</date></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">To the <addressee>Revd Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Knowing the interest you generally take in the<lb/> progress of Judaism&#44; I take the liberty of<lb/> <sic>adressing</sic> you in order to procure the aid<lb/> of your valuable services in obtaining<lb/> for us a competent person to<lb/> officiate in our congregation as <add>Hebrew</add> &#38;<lb/> lecturer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">So our congregation is yet in its<lb/> infancy&#44; &#38; not able to pay a <sic>heigh</sic><lb/> salary&#44; we have come to the conclusion<lb/> that the same person should also<lb/> fulfill the office of a teacher in<lb/> the <sic>hebrew</sic> and <sic>english</sic> languages &#40;as<lb/> hardly any of our children know how to<lb/> read the former&#41; in which case we<lb/> will be able to offer to pay a salary<lb/> of &#36;1000.00 to any such person coming<lb/> well recommended</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are anxious to procure such<lb/> a person as soon as possible as our new</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Synagogue is nearly done&#44; we<add>&#63;</add> rely much in<lb/> the aid of your valuable paper.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">So the Occident is but a periodical<lb/> We would suggest to you to advertise<lb/> in any other paper you would think<lb/> proper and charge to us.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A. Schval</persName> Presidt.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">of Kahl Adas Israel</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>To the</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><sic><addressee>Revd. Mr. Leeseser</addressee></sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
